==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Loach
<hw>Loach</hw> <pr>(l⟦omac⟧ch)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>loche</ets>, F. <ets>loche</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>Any one of several small, fresh-water, cyprinoid fishes of the
genera <gen>Cobitis</gen>, <gen>Nemachilus</gen>, and allied genera,
having six or more barbules around the mouth. They are found in Europe
and Asia. The common European species (<spn>Nemachilus barbatulus</spn>)
is used as a food fish.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

